ToDo_Task is a Django-based web application that allows you to manage and organize your tasks efficiently. With this application, you can create, update, and delete tasks, set deadlines, mark tasks as completed, and categorize them into different projects or categories.


Features
User Registration and Authentication: Users can register and create their accounts to securely log in and access their tasks.
Task Management: Users can create new tasks, update existing tasks, and delete tasks as needed. Each task can have a title, description, deadline, and completion status.
Task Categorization: Users can categorize tasks into different projects or categories for better organization and easier tracking.
Task Sorting and Filtering: Tasks can be sorted by deadline, completion status, or category, allowing users to prioritize and view tasks based on their preferences.
Notifications: Users receive notifications for approaching task deadlines to help them stay on top of their tasks.
User Profile: Each user has a profile page where they can view and update their personal information.


Installation
Clone the repository:
      git clone https://github.com/nimitshrestha/ToDo_Task.git

Navigate to the project directory:
      cd ToDo_Task

Create and activate a virtual environment (optional, but recommended):
      python -m venv env
      source env/bin/activate

Install the project dependencies:
      pip install -r requirements.txt

Perform database migrations:
      python manage.py makemigrations
      python manage.py migrate

Start the development server:
      python manage.py runserver
      Open your web browser and visit http://localhost:8000 to access the ToDo_Task application.

Configuration
The application can be configured by modifying the settings.py file located in the ToDo_Task directory. You can set the database configuration, email settings for notifications, and other relevant parameters.


Access APi:
path('<int:pk>/', DetailToDo.as_view()),    # <int:pk> is primary key or 'id'
path('show', ListToDo.as_view()),
path('create', CreateToDo.as_view()),
path('update/<int:pk>', UpdateToDo.as_view()),
path('delete/<int:pk>', DeleteToDo.as_view())


